OBX|2|TX|36813-4^CT Angiogram Chest for PE^LN|2|TECHNIQUE: Postcontrast helical CT Angiogram acquisition from lung bases to the apices with sagittal and coronal reformats at 2.5mm slice thickness. Maximal intensity projection images were created as part of this examination. CTDI(vol): 18.78 mGy. DLP: 359.99 mGy*cm. CT dose reduction technique utilized with one or more of the following: Automated exposure control and/or adjustment of the mA and/or kV according to patient size and/or use of iterative reconstruction technique. IV Contrast: 100 mL of Omnipaque 350 Complications: None.||||||F
OBX|3|TX|36813-4^CT Angiogram Chest for PE^LN|3|COMPARISON: None TECHNIQUE: Postcontrast helical CT Angiogram acquisition from lung bases to the apices with sagittal and coronal reformats at 2.5mm slice thickness. Maximal intensity projection images were created as part of this examination. CTDI(vol): 18.78 mGy. DLP: 359.99 mGy*cm. CT dose reduction technique utilized with one or more of the following: Automated exposure control and/or adjustment of the mA and/or kV according to patient size and/or use of iterative reconstruction technique. IV Contrast: 100 mL of Omnipaque 350 Complications: None.||||||F
OBX|4|FT|36813-4^CT Angiogram Chest for PE^LN|4|FINDINGS: There is no acute pulmonary embolism.\.br\\.br\There is dilation of the main pulmonary artery, which measures up\.br\to 3.6 cm in diameter.\.br\\.br\There is no thoracic aortic aneurysm.\.br\\.br\There is mediastinal and right hilar lymphadenopathy. For\.br\reference, a precarinal lymph node on series 2 image 158 measures\.br\3.0 x 1.5 cm. A right hilar lymph node on series 2 image 183\.br\measures 2.4 x 2.0 cm. A right infrahilar lymph node on series 2\.br\image 221 measures 1.6 x 1.7 cm.\.br\\.br\There is cardiomegaly. There is no pericardial effusion. There is\.br\atherosclerotic calcification of the coronary arteries.\.br\\.br\The visualized upper abdomen is unremarkable.\.br\\.br\There is no pulmonary consolidation, pleural effusion, or\.br\pneumothorax.\.br\\.br\There are scattered areas of abnormal groundglass density that\.br\are interspersed between normally aerated lung. There is mild\.br\interlobular septal thickening noted in the right upper lobe and\.br\left upper lobe.\.br\\.br\There is a 2.4 x 2.4 cm spiculated nodule noted in the right\.br\lower lobe on series 2 image 244. There are a few additional\.br\smaller pulmonary nodules noted in the right lung, the largest of\.br\which measures 6 mm and is located in the right lower lobe on\.br\series 2 image 303. Note is made of a 3 mm nodule in the right\.br\upper lobe on series 2 image 96.\.br\\.br\There is no suspicious lytic or blastic lesion.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|36813-4^CT Angiogram Chest for PE^LN|5|IMPRESSION: IMPRESSION: 1. No evidence of acute pulmonary embolism 2. A 2.4 x 2.4 cm spiculated nodule is noted in the right lower lobe. This is highly worrisome for a malignancy. 3. A few additional smaller pulmonary nodules are noted in the right lung, the largest of which measures 6 mm and is located in the right lower lobe. These are indeterminate in etiology. 4. There is mediastinal and right hilar lymphadenopathy as described above, which is nonspecific in etiology. 5. There are scattered areas of abnormal groundglass density that are interspersed between normally aerated lung. There is mild interlobular septal thickening noted in the right upper lobe and left upper lobe. In the acute setting, this could reflect pulmonary edema. Small vessel or small airways disease could also have a similar appearance. 6. Cardiomegaly 7. Abnormal dilation of the main pulmonary artery could be seen with pulmonary arterial hypertension||||||F
