OBX|2|FT|34552-0^Echocardiogram 2D with M-Mode^LN|2|FINDINGS: Left Ventricle: \.br\The left ventricular chamber size is normal.  There is mild to moderate \.br\left ventricular hypertrophy.  Global left ventricular wall motion and \.br\contractility are within normal limits.  The left ventricle appears \.br\hyperdynamic.  Doppler tissue E/e’ ratio suggests elevated mean left \.br\atrial pressure.  \.br\Left Atrium: \.br\The left atrium is mild to moderately dilated.   \.br\Right Ventricle: \.br\The right ventricular cavity size is normal.  The right ventricular \.br\global systolic function is hyperdynamic.  \.br\Right Atrium: \.br\The right atrium is mildly dilated.   \.br\Aortic Valve: \.br\The aortic valve is trileaflet.  Systolic excursion of the aortic valve \.br\cusps is reduced.  Mild aortic cusp sclerosis is present.  There is mild \.br\aortic regurgitation.   There is mild aortic stenosis.  The mean \.br\gradient of the aortic valve is 10 mmHg.   The aortic valve area, by \.br\VTI's, is calculated at 2.9 cm2.   \.br\Mitral Valve: \.br\There is posterior mitral annular calcification.  There is mild mitral \.br\regurgitation.   There is mild mitral stenosis.   The mean gradient \.br\across the mitral valve is 14 mmHg.   \.br\Tricuspid Valve: \.br\The tricuspid valve leaflets are normal.   There is a trace tricuspid \.br\regurgitation.   The right ventricular systolic pressure is calculated \.br\at 41 mmHg.   \.br\Pulmonic Valve: \.br\The pulmonic valve appears normal.  There is no evidence of pulmonic \.br\regurgitation.  \.br\Pericardium: \.br\There is no pericardial effusion.  \.br\Venous: \.br\The inferior vena cava appears normal in size.  There is a greater than \.br\50% respiratory change in the inferior vena cava dimension.\.br\\.br\Measurements:\.br\Name                    Value         Normal Range            \.br\LVPWd (MM)              0.95 cm       -                        \.br\LVIDd (MM)              4.73 cm       -                        \.br\LVIDs (MM)              2.49 cm       -                        \.br\LVIDd (MM) index        2.88 cm/m2    -                        \.br\LVIDs (MM) index        1.52 cm/m2    -                        \.br\LV FS (MM)              47.36 %       -                        \.br\LV FS Linear Derived (MM47.4 %        -                        \.br\EF Linear Derived (MM)  79 %          -                        \.br\Ao root diameter (MM)   2.3 cm        -                        \.br\LA dimension (AP) MM    4.8 cm        -                        \.br\LA:Ao ratio (MM)        2.09 ratio    -                        \.br\\.br\Name                    Value         Normal Range            \.br\RVIDd (AP) 2D           2.18 cm       -                        \.br\IVSd (2D)               1.2 cm        -                        \.br\LVPWd (2D)              1.3 cm        -                        \.br\LVIDd (2D)              3.6 cm        -                        \.br\LVIDs (2D)              1.6 cm        -                        \.br\Ao root diameter (2D)   3.1 cm        -                        \.br\LA dimension (AP) 2D    3.7 cm        -                        \.br\LA:Ao ratio (2D)        1.19 ratio    -                        \.br\Aortic root diameter (2D1.89 cm/m2    -                        \.br\LA dimension (2D) index 2.25 cm/m2    -                        \.br\\.br\Name                    Value         Normal Range            \.br\LA ESV SP 4CH (MOD)     72 ml         -                        \.br\LA ESV SP 2CH (MOD)     58 ml         -                        \.br\LA ESV BP (MOD)         65 ml         -                        \.br\LA ESV BP (MOD) index   39.61 ml/m2   -                        \.br\LV EDV SP 4CH (MOD)     46 ml         -                        \.br\LV ESV SP 4CH (MOD)     14 ml         -                        \.br\EF SP 4CH (MOD)         69.57 %       -                        \.br\LV EDV SP 2CH (MOD)     47 ml         -                        \.br\LV ESV SP 2CH (MOD)     7 ml          -                        \.br\EF SP 2CH (MOD)         85.11 %       -                        \.br\LV EDV BP               48 ml         -                        \.br\LV ESV BP               10 ml         -                        \.br\BP EF (MOD)             79.17 %       -                        \.br\LV EDV BP index         29.25 ml/m2   -                        \.br\LV ESV BP index         6.09 ml/m2    -                        \.br\LV mass (A/L)           117 g         -                        \.br\LV mass (A/L) index     71.3 g/m2     -                        \.br\\.br\Name                    Value         Normal Range            \.br\MV E-wave Vmax          2.6 m/sec     -                        \.br\MV deceleration time    238 msec      -                        \.br\MV A-wave Vmax          2.47 m/sec    -                        \.br\MV E:A ratio            1.05 ratio    -                        \.br\P. vein S-wave Vmax     0.28 m/sec    -                        \.br\P. vein D-wave Vmax     0.23 m/sec    -                        \.br\P. vein S:D Vmax ratio  1.18 ratio    -                        \.br\P. vein A-wave duration 180 msec      -                        \.br\LV septal e' Vmax       0.04 m/sec    -                        \.br\LV lateral e' Vmax      0.08 m/sec    -                        \.br\LV average e' Vmax      0.06 m/sec    -                        \.br\LV E:e' septal ratio    62.29 ratio   -                        \.br\LV E:e' lateral ratio   32.26 ratio   -                        \.br\LV average E:e' ratio   42.51 ratio   -                        \.br\\.br\Name                    Value         Normal Range            \.br\AV VTI                  40.1 cm       -                        \.br\AV mean gradient        10 mmHg       -                        \.br\LVOT diameter           2.2 cm        -                        \.br\LVOT VTI                31 cm         -                        \.br\LVOT mean gradient      5 mmHg        -                        \.br\DOI (VTI)               0.77 ratio    -                        \.br\SV LVOT                 117.78 ml     -                        \.br\CO LVOT                 12.37 l/min   -                        \.br\Cardiac index           7.54 l/min/m2 -                        \.br\AVA (continuity VTI)    2.9 cm2       -                        \.br\\.br\Name                    Value         Normal Range            \.br\MV VTI                  53.6 cm       -                        \.br\MV mean gradient        14 mmHg       -                        \.br\MV PHT                  74 msec       -                        \.br\MVA (PHT)               3 cm2         -                        \.br\MVA (continuity VTI)    2.2 cm2       -                        \.br\\.br\Name                    Value         Normal Range            \.br\TR Vmax                 3.09 m/sec    -                        \.br\TR peak gradient        38 mmHg       -                        \.br\RAP                     3 mmHg        -                        \.br\RVSP                    41 mmHg       -                        \.br\TAPSE                   3.1 cm        -                        \.br\IVC diameter            2.1 cm        -                        \.br\\.br\Name                    Value         Normal Range            \.br\PV VTI                  20.7 cm       -                        \.br\PV mean gradient        4 mmHg        -||||||F
OBX|3|TX|34552-0^Echocardiogram 2D with M-Mode^LN|3|IMPRESSION: Mild LVH with normal LV chamber size and hypercontractility of the LV with LVEF over 80%. There is significant mitral annulus calcification resulting in mild mitral stenosis, Peak diastolic gradiant about 25mmhg and mean about 14mmhg. Vavle area calculates to about 3.0cm2. There is significant calcification of the noncoronary cusp of the aortic valve with mild stenosis and mild regurgitation. Peak gradiant is 18mmhg and mean is 10mmhg. There is mild to moderate left atrial dilation. There is mild pulmonary HTN with a peak PA pressure about 40mmhg with no right sided chamber enlargemnt. IVC normal.||||||F
