OBR|5||ACC-P3-0005|24604-1^US Diagnostic Breast Left Limited^LN|||20180313093800||||||8mm l breast mass per PET.||||||||||||F
OBX|1|TX|24604-1^US Diagnostic Breast Left Limited^LN|1|CLINICAL INDICATION: 8mm l breast mass per PET.||||||F
OBX|2|FT|24604-1^US Diagnostic Breast Left Limited^LN|2|FINDINGS: Bilateral craniocaudad and oblique views of the breasts obtained digitally\.br\plus additional left MLO and left CC magnification compression spot views.\.br\Interpreted with CAD assistance.\.br\\.br\There is a roughly 1 cm nodule at central left breast which is similar to\.br\10/5/2015 and 6/10/2014.\.br\\.br\The current left MLO view demonstrates interval appearance of a second\.br\nodule cephalad to that measuring approximately 1 cm. Not well seen on the\.br\left CC screening view probably as it overlaps the other mass.\.br\\.br\Supplemental views left breast-compression spot views followed\.br\demonstrating the prior mass plus the second new mass in proximity to it.\.br\Not clear which of these two masses would correlate with the abnormal mass\.br\as reported on the 2/9/2018 PET scan though presumably the new mass would\.br\be the PET scan abnormality as the other is stable and would not be\.br\expected limited abnormal uptake on the PET scan.\.br\\.br\Left breast ultrasound-Ultrasound followed for further evaluation\.br\demonstrating 2 corresponding masses indication at the left breast 12:00\.br\position 3 cm the nipple. The first measures 9.3 x 7.7 mm in the antiradial\.br\plane, 8.2 x 8.0 mm in the radial plane, is hypoechoic with increased\.br\through transmission though is not a simple cyst as it contains internal\.br\echoes and a cleft or partial septation. Mild peripheral contour\.br\lobulations.\.br\\.br\The second mass is a benign-appearing simple cyst in the radial plane\.br\measuring 9.6 x 6.9 mm, antiradial plane 9.6 x 6.8 mm.  Also noted with\.br\limited scanning of the left axilla and axillary tail is a 1.3 cm diameter\.br\grossly benign-appearing left axillary node, multiple bilateral axillary\.br\nodes are present on the mammogram none of which particularly more\.br\suspicious than any other.||||||F
OBX|3|TX|24604-1^US Diagnostic Breast Left Limited^LN|3|IMPRESSION: Two left breast masses. One is stable and thus considered benign. The one which demonstrated PET scan abnormality is likely the new one which has arisen in proximity to the older one. Most likely the simple cyst would correlate with the more benign mammographic finding, and in the other mass possibly a fibroadenoma would correlate with the new mammographic finding. However given that the PET scan was reported as abnormal, further workup would be recommended. Suggest MRI left breast for additional evaluation. BI-RADS CATEGORY: 0 Incomplete: Additional imaging evaluation needed. THE PATIENT WILL BE NOTIFIED OF THESE RESULTS IN WRITING. RECOMMENDED FOLLOW-UP: Additional Imaging Evaluation Required BREAST DENSITY: Almost entirely fatty||||||F
ZDS|1.2.840.113619.2.55.3.3.5^NEWVUE_PACS^Application^DICOM
