OBX|1|TX|24604-1^US Diagnostic Breast Left Limited^LN|1|CLINICAL INDICATION: Follow-up for left breast densities/nodules||||||F
OBX|2|FT|24604-1^US Diagnostic Breast Left Limited^LN|2|FINDINGS: LEFT BREAST MAMMOGRAM: In the superior portion of left breast, 2\.br\oval-shaped densities are again noted, the larger one measures 10 mm in\.br\diameter unchanged since the prior study, and the smaller one measures 7\.br\mm, also unchanged.\.br\\.br\LEFT BREAST ULTRASOUND: At the site of the larger density seen on the\.br\mammogram and the prior ultrasound, there is a cyst measuring 10 x 8 mm,\.br\unchanged since 9 months ago.\.br\\.br\In the 12:00 position, 3 cm from the nipple, a small minimally lobulated\.br\hypoechoic nodule measures 10.1 x 6.0 mm radially (prior measurement 9.3 x\.br\7.7 mm), and 8.6 x 7.4 mm anti-radially (prior measurement 8.2 x 8.0 mm).\.br\This has the appearance of a fibroadenoma unchanged.\.br\\.br\It is recommend that the patient have a follow-up ultrasound in 12 months\.br\to document stability.||||||F
OBX|3|TX|24604-1^US Diagnostic Breast Left Limited^LN|3|IMPRESSION: 1. No change in appearance, or size of the small benign cyst. 2. No change in size of a hypoechoic nodule in the left breast compared with 03/13/18. No hypervascularity. The hypoechoic nodule has the appearance most likely of a small lobulated fibroadenoma. Recommend additional follow-up ultrasound study in 12 months (December 2019). BI-RADS CATEGORY: 3 Probably benign findings. Short interval follow-up suggested. THE PATIENT WILL BE NOTIFIED OF THESE RESULTS IN WRITING. RECOMMENDED FOLLOW-UP: 12-months follow up BREAST DENSITY: Scattered areas of fibroglandular density||||||F
