OBX|2|TX|36813-4^CT Angiogram Chest Non-Coronary^LN|2|TECHNIQUE: Postcontrast helical CT Angiogram acquisition from lung bases to the apices with sagittal and coronal reformats at 2.5mm slice thickness. Maximal intensity projection images were created as part of this examination. IV Contrast: 100 mL of Omnipaque 350 Complications: None. Total exam CT Dose Index 16.43 mGy Total exam Dose Length Product for a 312.27 mGy-cm CT dose reduction technique utilized with one or more of the following: Automated exposure control and/or adjustment of the mA and/or kV according to patient size and/or use of iterative reconstruction technique.||||||F
OBX|3|TX|36813-4^CT Angiogram Chest Non-Coronary^LN|3|COMPARISON: *** TECHNIQUE: Postcontrast helical CT Angiogram acquisition from lung bases to the apices with sagittal and coronal reformats at 2.5mm slice thickness. Maximal intensity projection images were created as part of this examination. IV Contrast: 100 mL of Omnipaque 350 Complications: None. Total exam CT Dose Index 16.43 mGy Total exam Dose Length Product for a 312.27 mGy-cm CT dose reduction technique utilized with one or more of the following: Automated exposure control and/or adjustment of the mA and/or kV according to patient size and/or use of iterative reconstruction technique.||||||F
OBX|4|FT|36813-4^CT Angiogram Chest Non-Coronary^LN|4|FINDINGS: Evaluation for pulmonary embolism in the segmental and\.br\subsegmental pulmonary arteries is nondiagnostic secondary to\.br\respiratory motion artifact. There is no central pulmonary\.br\embolism.\.br\\.br\There is no thoracic aortic aneurysm.\.br\\.br\There is mediastinal lymphadenopathy that has worsened in\.br\severity from the prior study. For reference, a subcarinal lymph\.br\node measures 3.7 x 2.1 cm. A precarinal lymph node measures 2.9\.br\x 1.6 cm.\.br\\.br\There is cardiomegaly with atherosclerotic calcification of the\.br\coronary arteries. Reflux of contrast into the IVC and hepatic\.br\veins could reflect an element of right heart failure. There is\.br\no pericardial effusion.\.br\\.br\The visualized upper abdomen is unremarkable.\.br\\.br\There are tiny bilateral pleural effusions, right greater than\.br\left.\.br\\.br\There has been interval increase in size of a mass within the\.br\right lower lobe as seen on series 2 image 276, measuring 3.8 x\.br\3.1 cm on today's study, previously measuring 2.4 x 2.5 cm on the\.br\examination from January 17, 2018.\.br\\.br\There is a 1.2 x 0.9 cm nodule in the right middle lobe on series\.br\2 image 286, new when compared to the prior study. A 0.8 x 0.5 cm\.br\pleural-based nodule in the left lower lobe on series 2 image 326\.br\is new when compared to the prior study. A 0.6 x 0.5 cm\.br\pleural-based nodule is noted in the right lower lobe on series 2\.br\image 343, new when compared to the prior study.\.br\\.br\There is diffuse interlobular septal thickening with scattered\.br\areas of groundglass opacity noted throughout the lungs.\.br\\.br\There is no pneumothorax.\.br\\.br\There is no suspicious lytic or blastic lesion. Degenerative\.br\changes are noted in the spine.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|36813-4^CT Angiogram Chest Non-Coronary^LN|5|IMPRESSION: IMPRESSION: 1. Evaluation for pulmonary embolism in the segmental and subsegmental pulmonary arteries is nondiagnostic secondary to respiratory motion artifact. There is no central pulmonary embolism. 2. Interval increase in size of a right lower lobe mass, now measuring 3.8 x 3.1 cm, worrisome for an underlying malignancy. There has been interval development of at least 3 pulmonary nodules noted in the right middle lobe, right lower lobe, and left lower lobe as described above, with worrisome for metastases. There has also been interval worsening of mediastinal lymphadenopathy, which could reflect metastatic disease. 3. Diffuse interlobular septal thickening with scattered areas of groundglass opacity are noted throughout the lungs. Given the presence of cardiomegaly, this is favored to reflect pulmonary edema, but please note that lymphangitic spread of tumor cannot be excluded 4. Reflux of contrast into the IVC and hepatic veins could reflect an element of right heart failure.||||||F
