OBX|2|FT|34552-0^Echocardiogram 2D with M-Mode^LN|2|FINDINGS: Left Ventricle: \.br\The left ventricular chamber size is normal.  There is moderate left \.br\ventricular hypertrophy.  The degree of left ventricular hypertrophy is \.br\categorized by mass index measurement.   Global left ventricular wall \.br\motion and contractility are within normal limits.  The left ventricle \.br\appears hyperdynamic.  The estimated ejection fraction is greater than \.br\65%.   The ejection fraction is calculated to be 81% using the Method of \.br\Disks.   Severely abnormal left ventricular diastolic function is \.br\observed.  \.br\Left Atrium: \.br\The left atrium is moderate to severely dilated.   \.br\Right Ventricle: \.br\The right ventricular cavity size is normal.  The right ventricular \.br\global systolic function is normal.  \.br\Right Atrium: \.br\The right atrium is mildly dilated.   \.br\Aortic Valve: \.br\Moderate aortic cusp sclerosis is present.  \.br\Mitral Valve: \.br\The mitral valve leaflets appear normal.  There is mitral annular \.br\calcification.  There is mild mitral regurgitation.   There is severe \.br\mitral stenosis.   \.br\Tricuspid Valve: \.br\The tricuspid valve leaflets are normal.   There is mild tricuspid \.br\regurgitation.  The right ventricular systolic pressure is calculated at \.br\58 mmHg.   There is no tricuspid stenosis.  \.br\Pulmonic Valve: \.br\The pulmonic valve appears normal.  There is no evidence of pulmonic \.br\regurgitation.  There is no pulmonic stenosis.   \.br\Pericardium: \.br\There is no pericardial effusion.  \.br\Venous: \.br\The inferior vena cava appears normal in size.  There is a greater than \.br\50% respiratory change in the inferior vena cava dimension.  CVP is \.br\estimated to be normal by IVC parameters.\.br\\.br\Measurements:\.br\Name                    Value         Normal Range            \.br\AV cusp separation (MM) 0.41 cm       -                        \.br\\.br\Name                    Value         Normal