OBX|4|FT|24627-2^CT Chest^LN|4|FINDINGS: There is a 3.1 x 3.8 x 2.8 cm mass in the right lower lung. On 2/8/2018 the\.br\mass measured 2.4 x 2.1 x 1.5 cm.\.br\\.br\There is a new 2.5 mm nodule in the right middle lobe series 3 axial image\.br\54.\.br\\.br\There is a stable 5 x 8 mm nodule in the right lower lobe on series 3 axial\.br\image 75.\.br\\.br\\.br\\.br\There is a stable 2.5 mm subpleural nodule in the anterior right middle\.br\lobe series 3 axial image 71.\.br\\.br\There is a stable 4 x 6 mm nodule in the left lower lobe subpleural\.br\location on series 3 axial image 81.\.br\\.br\There is bilateral hilar lymphadenopathy difficult to measure without\.br\intravenous contrast.\.br\\.br\There are mediastinal lymph nodes that are enlarged. There is a right\.br\paratracheal mediastinal lymph node measuring 1 cm previously measuring 0.8\.br\cm there is pretracheal mediastinal lymph node measuring 1.6 cm previously\.br\measuring 0.8 cm. There is a precarinal lymph node measuring 1.7 cm\.br\previously measuring 1.3 cm. There is a subcarinal lymph node measuring 1.9\.br\cm previously measuring 1.3 cm.\.br\\.br\There is diffuse increased interstitial lung markings thickening of the\.br\interlobar fissures or just may be related to heart disease or interstitial\.br\spread of cancer. There is cardiomegaly. There is coronary artery disease.\.br\There is densely calcified mitral valve annulus.\.br\\.br\In the upper abdomen there is thickened bilateral adrenal glands which are\.br\unchanged without discrete nodular mass.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24627-2^CT Chest^LN|5|IMPRESSION: Interval enlargement of right lower lobe pulmonary mass now measuring 3.1 x 3.8 x 2.8 cm compared with 2.4 x 2.1 x 1.5 cm on 2/8/2018. 1 apparent new 2.5 mm nodule in the right middle lobe. Multiple small bilateral stable nodules. Significant enlargement in mediastinal lymphadenopathy. Probable enlargement of bilateral hilar lymphadenopathy difficult to measure precisely due to absence of intravenous contrast. Stable appearance of the adrenal glands which are thickened but without any discrete nodular mass.||||||F
