OBX|3|TX|34552-0^Echocardiogram 2D with M-Mode^LN|3|IMPRESSION: Normal biventricular size and systolic function (LVEF 71%). Moderate left atrial enlargement. Severe mitral annular calcification with moderate to severe stenosis (mean gradient 12 mmHg). Mild aortic stenosis (mean gradient 16 mmHg). Mildly elevated estimated pulmonary artery systolic pressure of 46 mmHg based on an estimated central venous pressure of 3 mmHg. Compared with 4/21/21, the findings are similar, except estimated pulmonary artery systolic pressure slightly lower. Note: suggest repeat cardiology consult for further treatment and evaluation of mitral stenosis; the patient may benefit from slower heart rate for better left ventricular filling.||||||F
