OBX|4|FT|24590-2^MR Head^LN|4|FINDINGS: BRAIN PARENCHYMA: Ill-defined area of heterogeneous enhancement in the left frontal lobe measuring approximately 3.2 x 3.1 x 2.2 cm (TR by AP by SI). Small amount of susceptibility signal is identified along this enhancing abnormality suggestive of small hemorrhagic component. There is a necrotic component immediately superior to it measuring 1.3 x 2.1 x 1.3 cm. Surrounding vasogenic edema and mass effect. There is associated abnormal leptomeningeal enhancement in the left frontal and temporal lobes. \.br\ \.br\A rim-enhancing lesion measuring 5 mm seen in the right frontal lobe. \.br\ \.br\At least 2 enhancing lesions in the left cerebellum measuring 6 mm. Leptomeningeal enhancement along the cerebellar folia.\.br\ \.br\No acute infarct. No herniation. \.br\ \.br\VENTRICLES/EXTRA-AXIAL SPACES: No hydrocephalus or extra-axial fluid collections.\.br\ \.br\FLOW VOIDS: Intact.\.br\ \.br\EXTRACRANIAL STRUCTURES: Visualized structures are normal.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24590-2^MR Head^LN|5|IMPRESSION: Abnormal leptomeningeal enhancement in the cerebellum and left cerebral hemisphere. Ill-defined heterogeneous enhancing mass in the left frontal lobe measuring up to 3.2 cm with associated necrotic component. Additional tiny enhancing lesions in the right frontal lobe and left cerebellum. Findings are highly concerning for leptomeningeal and parenchymal metastatic disease. Per HC, there is a suspected lung mass on a CT chest from outside hospital.||||||F
