OBX|4|FT|24590-2^MR Head^LN|4|FINDINGS: Imaging is limited by motion artifact.\.br\ \.br\There is a region of parenchymal and leptomeningeal enhancement at the left frontal lobe which appears unchanged when compared to the previous exam. Leptomeningeal enhancement at the lateral left temporal lobe, along the superior cerebellar vermis, at the interpeduncular fossa, and at the bilateral internal auditory canals appears unchanged. Additional tiny foci of parenchymal enhancement at the left cerebellar hemisphere, right superior frontal gyrus, and parietal lobe appear unchanged.\.br\ \.br\There is a small enhancing calvarial focus at the right vertex which is unchanged. No new mass or abnormal enhancement is visualized. Small foci of susceptibility artifact associated with the left frontal lobe lesions appear unchanged. T2 hyperintense edema throughout left cerebral white matter appears unchanged.\.br\ \.br\There is mild diffuse parenchymal volume loss and bilateral periventricular white matter disease which appears unchanged. There is left greater than right mastoid fluid. No acute infarction is identified.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24590-2^MR Head^LN|5|IMPRESSION: Unchanged appearance of areas of parenchymal and leptomeningeal enhancement as previously described. No new lesion is identified.||||||F
